<h3>Question 15</h3>
<div><p><p>Find the vector x determined by the coordinate vector \([x]_{β} = \begin{bmatrix}-4\\ 8\\ 7\end{bmatrix}\) where \( β = \left \{ \begin{bmatrix}-1\\ 2\\ 0\end{bmatrix}, \begin{bmatrix}3\\ -5\\ 2\end{bmatrix}, \begin{bmatrix}4\\ -7\\ 3\end{bmatrix} \right \}\)</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Given,</p>
<p>[x]<sub>β</sub> = \(\begin{bmatrix}-4\\ 8\\ -7\end{bmatrix}\)</p>
<p>β = \(\left \{ \begin{bmatrix}-1\\ 2\\ 0\end{bmatrix}, \begin{bmatrix}3\\ -5\\ 2\end{bmatrix}, \begin{bmatrix}4\\ -7\\ 3\end{bmatrix} \right \}\)</p>
<p>Writing β in matrix form</p>
<p>β = \(\begin{bmatrix}-1 &amp; 3 &amp; 4\\ 2 &amp; -5 &amp; -7\\ 0 &amp; 2 &amp; 3\end{bmatrix}\)</p>
<p>Also, [x]<sub>β</sub> = \(\begin{bmatrix}-4\\ 8\\ -7\end{bmatrix}\)</p>
<p>We know,</p>
<p>x = β [x]<sub>β</sub></p>
<p>= \(\begin{bmatrix}-1 &amp; 3 &amp; 4\\ 2 &amp; -5 &amp; -7\\ 0 &amp; 2 &amp; 3\end{bmatrix}\) \(\begin{bmatrix}-4\\ 8\\ -7\end{bmatrix}\)</p>
<p>= \(\begin{bmatrix}4 + 24 &#8211; 28\\ -8 &#8211; 40 + 49\\ 0 + 16 &#8211; 21\end{bmatrix}\)</p>
<p>=\(\begin{bmatrix}0\\ 1\\ -5\end{bmatrix}\)</p>
<p>Therefore, Vector x = \(\begin{bmatrix}0\\ 1\\ -5\end{bmatrix}\)</p>
</div>
